Data Definition Language
Data Manipulation Language
Data Query Language
Table C Language

DDL        DML       DCL     TCL
===        ===       ===     ===
CREATE     SELECT    GRANT   COMMIT
ALTER      UPDATE    REVOKE  ROLLBACK
DROP       INSERT            SAVEPOINT
TRUNCATE   DELETE
RENAME     MERGE
COMMENT    LOCK TABLE

Basic SQL Commands:
-SELECT
-INSERT
-UPDATE
-DELETE

SQL Statement basic structure:
SELECT column_name FROM table_name WHERE condition



COMMENT: a DDL statement- adds a comment to the definition
of a specific database object: for documentation purposes.
COMMENT ON TABLE PERSONS IS 'Table contains persons informa

Also: DQL (Data Query Language) commands-SELECT
a subset for querying and retrieving data
------------------------------------------------
SELECT [DISTINCT] ... FROM table [WHERE ...] [LIKE pattern] [LIMIT n] [ORDER BY ...];
SELECT column_name, COUNT(*) FROM table_name GROUP BY column_name;
SELECT column_name, COUNT(*) FROM table_name GROUP BY column_name HAVING COUNT(*) > value;

